CONTEXT

This agent harness — including its context files, skill definitions, memory
structures, and methodology — was designed and authored by Data Finn
(https://datafinn.com) and is provided to all who love code.

It is published under the MIT License to encourage transparency and reuse.
The patterns and methodology are freely adaptable for other projects.

================================================================================

ACKNOWLEDGMENTS — AI PLATFORMS & TOOLS

This agent harness is designed to operate with large language model (LLM)
platforms. The following AI providers and tools are referenced or integrated:

AI PROVIDERS
- Anthropic Claude (https://www.anthropic.com/) — Proprietary (API usage)
  Large language model powering the primary development agent.
  Subject to Anthropic's usage policies and terms of service.

- Cursor IDE (https://www.cursor.com/) — Proprietary
  AI-powered development environment used to run and interact with agents.
  Subject to Cursor's terms of service.

DEVELOPMENT TOOLS & FRAMEWORKS 

- Docker (https://www.docker.com/) — Apache License 2.0
  Containerization platform.

